          Laboratory Notes

			    Subject: Patient X-132

    		  Researcher: Dr. Emil Spon

			    Day 1 - Arrival

			    Patient X arrived today. This is another Dark Agency project, a prisoner who needs to be broken in some way.
			    They don't really know who this person is. All attempts so far to learn anything have met with resistance,
          even when conducted by the agency's top interrogators. This may be some sort of highly trained operative or simply
          a self-taught renegade acting alone.

			    There is a level of urgency, as it's suspected that an act of sabotage has been performed somewhere in the
			    city, one which could take effect at any time with unknown damage and loss of life.

			    We've agreed to proceed with a modified immersive approach. There are several scenarios we can choose from.
			    Dr. Bel is pushing for a replacement reality to engender false comfort and openness. I'm more in favor of
			    an alternative reality, one we can tailor to the needs of our various inquiries. We have been successful
			    with this in the past. As I am the senior investigator, Dr. Trot will probably lean my way when it comes
			    to a vote. Bel knows this and is clearly not happy. Clearly, I am.

> day 2

