          Laboratory Notes

			    Subject: Patient X-132

    		  Researcher: Dr. Emil Spon

			    Day 2 - Preparation

			    Patient X has been sedated overnight in preparation for immersion. I will be taking part directly in the simulation. Drs. Bel and Trot have declined, for differing reasons. In order to keep the construction to a minimum, and due to the lack of available persons, the alternative reality will be set in a prison cell, which Patient X and I will share. Patient X will be a new prisoner, and I will be the current cell occupant.

			    In order to heighten the threat response, the prison will be fantastical, with engineered creatures to plague the cellmates. We will play on common human fears -
          confinement, spiders, crawling creatures, darkness.

			    The alternative reality will need to have a correspondence, so that we can map responses back to the real world.
          That's the only way we'll be able to extract the necessary information.

> today

